The paper discusses the development of a mathematical query language for formal libraries, which involves the use of artificial intelligence (AI) and deep learning (DL) techniques to enable efficient search and retrieval of mathematical knowledge. The paper also discusses the use of information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML) techniques to improve the scalability and expressivity of the query language. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of logical formalisms and databases (DB) to support the indexing and querying of mathematical libraries. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.LG, and cs.DB.
